More than 10,000 Muslims on Sunday met in Mamburui, Magarini subcounty, to mark the 54th anniversary of former scholar Al Habib Said.They were drawn from Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda, Burundi and even Saudi Arabia.They marched in the town, singing songs of praise before holding prayers at the graveside of Said.Politicians present included Kilifi Senator Stewart Madzayo and Nyali MP hopeful Omar Masumbuko.Many Muslim scholars have their roots in Mamburui.Faithful Mushamu Mohamed said the celebrations are held annually since Said's death.Hassan Wazir from Saudi Arabia said he was happy to attend the anniversary.&ldquo;We got a chance to meet many Muslim brothers from Mamburui and Malindi," he said. Senator Madzayo said it was a great opportunity to join the Muslims in their celebrations.